cs.DS, cs.CC, cs.IT, cs.NA, cs.SI. 

The paper deals with an optimization problem related to graph theory and algorithms, which suggests that it could belong to several sub-categories. The use of approximation algorithms and the analysis of their performance ratio points towards cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.CC (Computational Complexity). The mention of dynamic edge weights and the comparison to the traveling salesman problem suggest cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.NA (Numerical Analysis). Finally, the use of novel schemes and structural properties suggests cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
